  "executive_brief_md": "## TMEM173 \u2014 stimulator of interferon response cGAMP interactor 1\n\n**White Space score 55.81/100 \u00b7 rank 1/13 \u00b7 MEDIUM confidence.** Top-tier white space \u2014 validated, tractable, and comparatively uncrowded within the IO cohort.\n\nTMEM173 is a basal body target in the immuno-oncology cohort with no approved drug yet. Development level **Tchem**; mechanism: Stimulator of interferon genes protein agonist. Competitive footprint: 2 industry sponsor(s) in trials. Leading disease associations: STING-associated vasculopathy with onset in infancy, COVID-19, dengue disease, hypothyroidism.\n\n**Score decomposition** \u2014 Validation 0.7418, Tractability 0.9, Saturation 0.1641 (cohort-normalized). The score is multiplicative, so crowding drives it down even when biology is validated \u2014 which is why saturated checkpoints sit low and validated-but-uncrowded targets rise.\n\n*Every figure above resolves to a versioned source in the Provenance tab. This brief is model-written (claude-fable-5) over sourced facts only.*",
